        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI envision the filter classes working somewhat like Builder classes, where you can chain a bunch of setXxx() methods together, ex:\n\n  new PdpGroupFilter()\n    .setLatestVersion()\n    .setState(ACTIVE)\n    .setSupportsType(typeName, typeVersion)\n    .hasActivePdps()\n      // last one implies that the subgroups supporting the\n      // policy type/version each have active PDPs",
